  "name": "LED Fade-On Circuit",
  "lesson": {
    "title": "LED Fade-On Circuit",
    "description": "USB → slide switch → 1kΩ → split: red LED on the center column and 1000µF cap on the east branch in parallel. Flip the switch on — the LED starts dim and brightens over several seconds as the capacitor charges (fade-on). Flip off to see it fade out. Layout swaps lesson 21 (cap center, LED east); the LED is on the center column here. LED at 90° (anode north); cap + toward power."
  },
